The northwind database is a demo database which consists of 4 tables namely products, customers, orders and order details. Each of the table has various columns. 
The first table named products has 10 columns namely product_id of type smallint, product_name of type character, supplier_id of type smallint, category_id of type smallint, quantity_per_unit of type character, unit_price of type real, units_on_stock of type smallint, reorder_level of type smallint and discontinued of type integer. It has a total of 77 rows/entries. 
The second table named customers has 11 columns namely customer_id of type character, company_name of type character, contact_name of type character, address of type character, city of type character, region of type character, postal_code of type character, country of type character, phone of type character, fax of type character. It has a total of 91 rows/entries.
The third table named orders has 14 columns namely order_id of type smallint, customer_id of type character, employee_id of type smallint, order_date of type date, required_date of type date, shipped_date of type date, ship_via of type smallint, freight of type real, ship_name of type character, ship_address of type character, ship_city of type character, ship_region of type character, ship_postal_code of type character and ship_country of type character. It has a total of 830 rows/entries.
The fourth table named order_details has 5 columns namely order_id of type smallint which is also a primary key, product_id of type smallint which is another primary key, unit_price of type real, quantity of type smallint, discount of type real. It has a total of 2155 rows/entries. 
